snippet.textDisplay: America's race tracks are an integral part of America's history.  I love the fact that you are restoring history in your neck of the woods, unlike our jackass former mayor of OKC who despite public outcry, eliminated our race track.  A poor man could feed and entertain his whole family on the cheap at the OKC Fairgrounds Race Track.  I know you have a lot of money invested and have to recover it, but try to keep the lower income fans in mind when it comes to pricing your concessions.  If a man can afford to bring his family, you're developing the future generations of race fans.  Wish I lived close.  I would volunteer my social separation time behind a power washer just to be a part of it, because.............America!

snippet.textDisplay:
I love how Cletus is getting so into this, and showing us how much actually goes into making a good place for us to actually enjoy Vehicles. Often times we just pull up to an empty parking lot lay down some tire marks on some asphalt but we don't even really think about the ground that were enjoying.

On another note I have to crack a giggle at watching all the dudes take a break about halfway through the video for some reason that shit was funny cuz I think car enthusiasts and construction workers have something in common when you're working out in the sun whether you're cranking on a car or building something or doing any sort of manual labor really we all can appreciate sitting down wherever we can fit our asses and shoving something down their stomach
